England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"Abt 1060–1093":"omkring 1060–1093","1058–1093":"1058–1093","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1060–1093":"1060–1093","1090":"1090","1058":"1058","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1150":"1150","Abt 1060":"omkring 1060","1083":"1083","1093":"1093","1060":"1060","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, England","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster, Lancashire, England":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster district, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"Abt 1060–1093":"circa 1060–1093","1058–1093":"1058–1093","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1060–1093":"1060–1093","1090":"1090","1058":"1058","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1150":"1150","Abt 1060":"circa 1060","1083":"1083","1093":"1093","1060":"1060","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, England","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster, Lancashire, England":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster district, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1060–1093":"about 1060–1093","1058–1093":"1058–1093","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1060–1093":"1060–1093","1090":"1090","1058":"1058","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1150":"1150","Abt 1060":"about 1060","1083":"1083","1093":"1093","1060":"1060","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, England","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster, Lancashire, England":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster district, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Perrin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French and English: from the Old French and Middle English personal name <i>Perrin</i>, a pet form of Old French <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Perine  ,   Perrine  , and   Prine  .","History: Henri Perrin from Louargat in Côtes-d'Armor, Brittany (France), married Jeanne Merrin in Montreal, QC, in 1661. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its variants or altered forms <i>Perrine</i> and <i>Pareyn</i>) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America. One of the Huguenot ancestors was Daniel Perrin (1642–1719), nicknamed <i>The Huguenot</i>, who arrived in New York in 1665, aboard the <i>Philip</i>, and settled first in NJ and later on Staten Island. Among his descendants the surname is common in the altered forms <i>Perrine</i>, <i>Perine</i> and <i>Prine</i>. The Staten Island community of Huguenot is named after Daniel Perrin and other Huguenots who settled in the area during the late 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Prine","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Perrin  .","In some cases also an Americanized form of Dutch   Pruyn   or perhaps of some other similar (like-sounding) surname.","History: The surname <i>Prine</i> is established among the descendants of the Huguenot immigrant Daniel Perrin (1642–1719); see   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Pierre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Antoine, Yves, Michel, Jean Claude, Mireille, Jean Robert, Francois, Monique, Raoul, Serge.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian:","from the personal name <i>Pierre</i>, French form of   Peter   (see also below). This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Jean   and   Joseph  ) and in Saint Martin. It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in Trinidad and Tobago, Saint Lucia, Grenada, and Bahamas)."]},{"name":"Perren","meanings":["French and English (of French Huguenot origin): variant of   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Parren","meanings":["English: variant of   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Perrine","meanings":["French: from the feminine form of   Perrin   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","English: variant of   Perrin  . This surname is now rare in Britain and Ireland.","History: The surname <i>Perrine</i> of French origin (see 1 above) is listed along with its original form   Perrin   in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Parran","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Monique.","Altered form of French   Perrin  . This surname was brought to England by the Huguenots, but has died out there.","In some cases possibly also southern French: topographic name from Occitan <i>parran</i> ‘small garden behind a house’. This surname is very rare in France."]},{"name":"Perrins","meanings":["English (West Midlands): variant of   Perrin  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Bette","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Bet  , associated particularly with the film actress  Bette Davis  (  1908–89 ), whose original name was  Ruth Elizabeth Davis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":6,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":26,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Bette Perrin was born about 1060, in Halton, Cheshire, England. She married Ralph de Garnet in 1083, in Lancaster, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1093, in Lancaster, Lancashire, England, at the age of 34."},"et":{"Abt 1060–1093":"umbes 1060–1093","1058–1093":"1058–1093","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1060–1093":"1060–1093","1090":"1090","1058":"1058","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1150":"1150","Abt 1060":"umbes 1060","1083":"1083","1093":"1093","1060":"1060","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, England","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster, Lancashire, England":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster district, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1060–1093":"noin 1060–1093","1058–1093":"1058–1093","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1060–1093":"1060–1093","1090":"1090","1058":"1058","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1150":"1150","Abt 1060":"noin 1060","1083":"1083","1093":"1093","1060":"1060","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, England","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster, Lancashire, England":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Halton-with-Aughton, Lancaster district, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1060–1093":"environ 1060–1093","1058–1093":"1058–1093","109